{"id":622,"date":"2021-04-09T23:09:24","date_gmt":"2021-04-09T23:09:24","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/programming.sdarobotics.org\/?page_id=622"},"modified":"2021-04-10T03:27:33","modified_gmt":"2021-04-10T03:27:33","slug":"encoder-board","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/encoder-board\/","title":{"rendered":"Encoder Board"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>In this chapter we are going to cover assembling&nbsp;the Arduino Board. The encoder board will be used to measure the rotation of the wheels. This will enable us to measure how far the robot travels as well as it\u2019s speed.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You will need the following parts.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderParts.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderParts.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-625\" width=\"330\" height=\"203\" srcset=\"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderParts.jpg 500w, http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderParts-300x184.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 330px) 100vw, 330px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Place one of the potentiometers on the board as shown below. Hold it in place with one of your fingers and carefully solder the three connectors on the front and the one on the back. Be careful not to solder over the three holes next to the pot.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderPotFront.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderPotFront.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-627\" width=\"327\" height=\"276\" srcset=\"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderPotFront.jpg 500w, http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderPotFront-300x254.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 327px) 100vw, 327px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>When complete it should look like:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderPotComplete.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderPotComplete.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-629\" width=\"330\" height=\"259\" srcset=\"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderPotComplete.jpg 500w, http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderPotComplete-300x236.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 330px) 100vw, 330px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now flip the board over and solder the second potentiometers on the reverse side in the same manner:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderPotReverse.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderPotReverse.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-631\" width=\"330\" height=\"218\" srcset=\"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderPotReverse.jpg 500w, http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderPotReverse-300x199.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 330px) 100vw, 330px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now insert the two resisters into their proper position and hold them in place with tape:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderResistorPlacement.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderResistorPlacement.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-632\" width=\"326\" height=\"235\" srcset=\"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderResistorPlacement.jpg 500w, http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderResistorPlacement-300x216.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 326px) 100vw, 326px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Then flip the board over and solder them in place. After you have soldered them, cut off the excess leads.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now position the right angle header as shown below and solder&nbsp;<strong>only<\/strong>&nbsp;one pin:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderHeaderSolder.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderHeaderSolder.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-633\" width=\"330\" height=\"292\" srcset=\"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderHeaderSolder.jpg 500w, http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderHeaderSolder-300x266.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 330px) 100vw, 330px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Once that pin is soldered, pick up the board and make sure that the connector is seated properly. If it is not, you can adjust it by heating the pin you just soldered. When heating the pin, make sure that you are not touching the pin that you are heating:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderHeaderAdjust.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderHeaderAdjust.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-634\" width=\"330\" height=\"242\" srcset=\"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderHeaderAdjust.jpg 500w, http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderHeaderAdjust-300x221.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 330px) 100vw, 330px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Your final board should now look like:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderComplete.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderComplete.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-635\" width=\"326\" height=\"311\" srcset=\"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderComplete.jpg 534w, http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/EncoderComplete-300x287.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 326px) 100vw, 326px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Repeat this process for the second encoder board.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>In this chapter we are going to cover assembling&nbsp;the Arduino Board. The encoder board will be used to measure the rotation of the wheels. This will enable us to measure how far the robot travels as well as it\u2019s speed. You will need the following parts. Place one of the potentiometers on the board as&hellip;&nbsp;<a href=\"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/encoder-board\/\" class=\"\" rel=\"bookmark\">Read More &raquo;<span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Encoder Board<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","template":"","meta":{"neve_meta_sidebar":"","neve_meta_container":"","neve_meta_enable_content_width":"","neve_meta_content_width":0,"neve_meta_title_alignment":"","neve_meta_author_avatar":"","neve_post_elements_order":"","neve_meta_disable_header":"","neve_meta_disable_footer":"","neve_meta_disable_title":""},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/622"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=622"}],"version-history":[{"count":5,"href":"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-js